Function Reference/url shorten « WordPress Codex
-----------

Shortens URLs. Removes `http://`, `www.`, and truncates the remaining
URL to 35 characters, including '...' if the URL is longer than that.

WordPress uses it to display URLs on the [link management
screen](/Links_Manager "Links Manager").

Usage
-----

`  <?php echo url_shorten('http://www.example.com/an/article/with/a/very/long/url'); ?> `

This would print:

`  example.com/an/article/with/a/ve... `

Parameters
----------

 `$url` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) URL that is being shortened.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   The shortened URL.

Changelog
---------

Since: 1.2.1

Source File
-----------

`url_shorten()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/misc.php`.

